"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-paris-olympics-perfectly-captured-spirit-of-host-city\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 The signs hanging outside the apartment windows on Rue Lepic say A VENDRE.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 84, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 61, \"end\": 70, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rue_Lepic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rue Lepic\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rue_Lepic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rue_Lepic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PARIS\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 5}, {\"ngram\": \"The signs\", \"from\": 10, \"to\": 19}, {\"ngram\": \"the apartment windows\", \"from\": 36, \"to\": 57}, {\"ngram\": \"A VENDRE\", \"from\": 75, \"to\": 83}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The listing says Vincent Van Gogh lived there from 1886 to 1888.\", \"from\": 85, \"to\": 149, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 102, \"end\": 109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.926910475262851e-44, \"text\": \"Vincent\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The listing\", \"from\": 85, \"to\": 96}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In many cities, this would be a prime tourist attraction.\", \"from\": 150, \"to\": 207, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many cities\", \"from\": 153, \"to\": 164}, {\"ngram\": \"a prime tourist attraction\", \"from\": 180, \"to\": 206}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Paris, it is an apartment for sale.\", \"from\": 208, \"to\": 246, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 211, \"end\": 216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.981077526137568e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an apartment\", \"from\": 224, \"to\": 236}, {\"ngram\": \"sale\", \"from\": 241, \"to\": 245}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The city\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s cultural soil is too rich to build a museum on every block where one belongs.\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 337, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The city\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s cultural soil\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 273}, {\"ngram\": \"a museum\", \"from\": 295, \"to\": 303}, {\"ngram\": \"every block\", \"from\": 307, \"to\": 318}, {\"ngram\": \"one\", \"from\": 325, \"to\": 328}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was here that Van Gogh painted \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cView From Theo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Apartment,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d which is now on display at the Van Gogh Museum in Amsterdam, though the notion of a Van Gogh Museum would have seemed laughable at the time, and perhaps not even appealing to the artist: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cTo succeed you have to have ambition,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Vincent once wrote to his brother Theo, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cand ambition seems absurd to me.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Van Gogh lived in Theo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s apartment and off his brother\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s largesse.\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 790, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 440, \"end\": 455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Van_Gogh_Museum\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Van Gogh Museum\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Van_Gogh_Museum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Van_Gogh_Museum\"}, {\"begin\": 459, \"end\": 468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7060043648644086e-23, \"text\": \"Amsterdam\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\"}, {\"begin\": 493, \"end\": 508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Van_Gogh_Museum\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Van Gogh Museum\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Van_Gogh_Museum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Van_Gogh_Museum\"}, {\"begin\": 640, \"end\": 647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.926910475262851e-44, \"text\": \"Vincent\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\"}, {\"begin\": 674, \"end\": 678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Theseus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.353201950745516e-16, \"text\": \"Theo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Theseus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Theseus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Van Gogh\", \"from\": 356, \"to\": 364}, {\"ngram\": \"Theo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Apartment\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 404}, {\"ngram\": \"display\", \"from\": 425, \"to\": 432}, {\"ngram\": \"the notion\", \"from\": 477, \"to\": 487}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 548}, {\"ngram\": \"the artist\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 594}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cTo\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 601}, {\"ngram\": \"ambition\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 635}, {\"ngram\": \"his brother\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 673}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cand ambition\", \"from\": 680, \"to\": 695}, {\"ngram\": \"me.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Van Gogh\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 727}, {\"ngram\": \"Theo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s apartment\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 755}, {\"ngram\": \"his brother\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s largesse\", \"from\": 764, \"to\": 788}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He did not sell a single painting.\", \"from\": 791, \"to\": 825, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a single painting\", \"from\": 807, \"to\": 824}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once, he tried to stage an art exhibition at a restaurant called Petit Boulevard.\", \"from\": 826, \"to\": 907, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an art exhibition\", \"from\": 850, \"to\": 867}, {\"ngram\": \"a restaurant\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 883}, {\"ngram\": \"Petit Boulevard\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 906}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to the Van Gogh Letters project, the evening ended with \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009ca violent altercation between the owner and Vincent,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d who placed all the paintings in a wheelbarrow and pulled them back to the apartment that is nowa vendre.\", \"from\": 908, \"to\": 1137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1021, \"end\": 1028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.926910475262851e-44, \"text\": \"Vincent\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Van Gogh Letters project\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 949}, {\"ngram\": \"the evening\", \"from\": 951, \"to\": 962}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009ca violent altercation\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 998}, {\"ngram\": \"the owner\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1016}, {\"ngram\": \"all the paintings\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1061}, {\"ngram\": \"a wheelbarrow\", \"from\": 1065, \"to\": 1078}, {\"ngram\": \"the apartment\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1116}, {\"ngram\": \"nowa vendre\", \"from\": 1125, \"to\": 1136}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere in Paris, a young man who didnotthink ambition seemed absurd was still refining his own.\", \"from\": 1139, \"to\": 1237, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1152, \"end\": 1157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.981077526137568e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a young man\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1170}, {\"ngram\": \"ambition\", \"from\": 1187, \"to\": 1195}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pierre de Coubertin had read about the ancient Olympics in school, and he firmly believed proper schooling should include physical exercise\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094a belief that contradicted Parisian society at the time.\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1238, \"end\": 1257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pierre de Coubertin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ancient Olympics\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1293}, {\"ngram\": \"school\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1303}, {\"ngram\": \"proper schooling\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1344}, {\"ngram\": \"physical exercise\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094a belief\", \"from\": 1360, \"to\": 1388}, {\"ngram\": \"Parisian society\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1423}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1435}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But he had not yet solidified the idea that would later be attributed to him: A sporting event among nations around the world.\", \"from\": 1437, \"to\": 1563, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 1467, \"to\": 1475}, {\"ngram\": \"A sporting event\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1531}, {\"ngram\": \"nations\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1545}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1562}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their passions would pull them out of Paris.\", \"from\": 1565, \"to\": 1609, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1603, \"end\": 1608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.981077526137568e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their passions\", \"from\": 1565, \"to\": 1579}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Van Gogh would go south to Arles, where he would have one of the most extraordinary creative periods in human history, but not what he really sought: An artist\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s colony that brought peace to his brain.\", \"from\": 1610, \"to\": 1813, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1637, \"end\": 1642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"score\": 0.9999910515580466, \"rank\": 8.948521647303654e-06, \"text\": \"Arles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Van Gogh\", \"from\": 1610, \"to\": 1618}, {\"ngram\": \"the most extraordinary creative periods\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1710}, {\"ngram\": \"human history\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1727}, {\"ngram\": \"An artist\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s colony\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1780}, {\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 1794, \"to\": 1799}, {\"ngram\": \"his brain\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1812}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Coubertin would go on trips to England and the United States, to study the role of sport.\", \"from\": 1814, \"to\": 1903, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1845, \"end\": 1852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England\", \"score\": 0.8866910281927028, \"rank\": 0.12778569847374535, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England\"}, {\"begin\": 1861, \"end\": 1874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999851734175, \"rank\": 1.4818627101826614e-08, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Coubertin\", \"from\": 1814, \"to\": 1823}, {\"ngram\": \"trips\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1841}, {\"ngram\": \"the role\", \"from\": 1885, \"to\": 1893}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 1897, \"to\": 1902}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the 1889 World\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Fair in Paris, as visitors climbed the brand-new Eiffel Tower, Coubertin organized the Congress on Questions of Physical Education.\", \"from\": 1905, \"to\": 2058, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1935, \"end\": 1940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.981077526137568e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 1889 World\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Fair\", \"from\": 1908, \"to\": 1931}, {\"ngram\": \"visitors\", \"from\": 1945, \"to\": 1953}, {\"ngram\": \"the brand-new Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1988}, {\"ngram\": \"Coubertin\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 1999}, {\"ngram\": \"the Congress\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2022}, {\"ngram\": \"Questions\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2035}, {\"ngram\": \"Physical Education\", \"from\": 2039, \"to\": 2057}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Painter Paul Gauguin, who had joined Van Gogh for a tumultuous period in Arles that ended with Van Gogh severing his own ear, held an exhibition on the grounds of the World\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Fair.\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2241, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2067, \"end\": 2079, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Gauguin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.157901627205169e-67, \"text\": \"Paul Gauguin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Gauguin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Gauguin\"}, {\"begin\": 2132, \"end\": 2137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"score\": 0.9999910515580466, \"rank\": 8.948521647303654e-06, \"text\": \"Arles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_van_Gogh\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Van Gogh\", \"from\": 2096, \"to\": 2104}, {\"ngram\": \"a tumultuous period\", \"from\": 2109, \"to\": 2128}, {\"ngram\": \"Van Gogh\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2162}, {\"ngram\": \"his own ear\", \"from\": 2172, \"to\": 2183}, {\"ngram\": \"an exhibition\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2203}, {\"ngram\": \"the grounds\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2218}, {\"ngram\": \"the World\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Fair\", \"from\": 2222, \"to\": 2240}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The next year, Van Gogh completed the only art sale of his lifetime, getting 400 francs from a friend for \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe Red Vineyard.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009dThree months later, his mind finally lost him for good: He shot himself in the chest with a revolver.\", \"from\": 2243, \"to\": 2473, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Van Gogh\", \"from\": 2258, \"to\": 2266}, {\"ngram\": \"the only art sale\", \"from\": 2277, \"to\": 2294}, {\"ngram\": \"his lifetime\", \"from\": 2298, \"to\": 2310}, {\"ngram\": \"400 francs\", \"from\": 2320, \"to\": 2330}, {\"ngram\": \"a friend\", \"from\": 2336, \"to\": 2344}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe Red Vineyard.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009dThree\", \"from\": 2349, \"to\": 2377}, {\"ngram\": \"his mind\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2400}, {\"ngram\": \"the chest\", \"from\": 2447, \"to\": 2456}, {\"ngram\": \"a revolver\", \"from\": 2462, \"to\": 2472}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two years later, in a speech at the Sorbonne on Paris\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s left bank, Coubertin delivered a speech that ended with a request for help with \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cthis grandiose and beneficent work: the re-establishment of the Olympic Games.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Van Gogh and Coubertin continue to influence society in ways neither man could possibly have imagined.\", \"from\": 2474, \"to\": 2800, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a speech\", \"from\": 2494, \"to\": 2502}, {\"ngram\": \"the Sorbonne\", \"from\": 2506, \"to\": 2518}, {\"ngram\": \"Paris\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s left bank\", \"from\": 2522, \"to\": 2541}, {\"ngram\": \"Coubertin\", \"from\": 2543, \"to\": 2552}, {\"ngram\": \"a speech\", \"from\": 2563, \"to\": 2571}, {\"ngram\": \"a request\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2597}, {\"ngram\": \"help\", \"from\": 2602, \"to\": 2606}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cthis grandiose and beneficent work\", \"from\": 2612, \"to\": 2649}, {\"ngram\": \"establishment\", \"from\": 2658, \"to\": 2671}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Van Gogh\", \"from\": 2675, \"to\": 2705}, {\"ngram\": \"Coubertin\", \"from\": 2710, \"to\": 2719}, {\"ngram\": \"society\", \"from\": 2742, \"to\": 2749}, {\"ngram\": \"ways\", \"from\": 2753, \"to\": 2757}, {\"ngram\": \"neither man\", \"from\": 2758, \"to\": 2769}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics that just concluded owe an enormous debt to both.\", \"from\": 2801, \"to\": 2863, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 2801, \"to\": 2813}, {\"ngram\": \"an enormous debt\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 2854}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As much as any people in the world, Parisians believe in art as something that should be experienced communally but absorbed individually.\", \"from\": 2865, \"to\": 3003, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any people\", \"from\": 2876, \"to\": 2886}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2890, \"to\": 2899}, {\"ngram\": \"Parisians\", \"from\": 2901, \"to\": 2910}, {\"ngram\": \"art\", \"from\": 2922, \"to\": 2925}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 2929, \"to\": 2938}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These Olympics were an expression of that.\", \"from\": 3004, \"to\": 3046, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These Olympics\", \"from\": 3004, \"to\": 3018}, {\"ngram\": \"an expression\", \"from\": 3024, \"to\": 3037}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony was more open than it ever has been: They included the Eiffel Tower, Trocadero, the Seine, and Tuileries Garden, and the torch was passed from French soccer legend Zinedine Zidane to stars who hail from other countries before being returned to the French.\", \"from\": 3047, \"to\": 3323, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3137, \"end\": 3146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Trocadero\", \"score\": 0.9999999986475814, \"rank\": 1.3431656194884332e-09, \"text\": \"Trocadero\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Trocadero\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Trocadero\"}, {\"begin\": 3152, \"end\": 3157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.464505079426721e-30, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 3163, \"end\": 3179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuileries_Garden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tuileries Garden\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuileries_Garden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuileries_Garden\"}, {\"begin\": 3211, \"end\": 3217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9976549912753273, \"rank\": 0.002080445165442114, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3232, \"end\": 3247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zinedine Zidane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\"}, {\"begin\": 3316, \"end\": 3322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9976549912753273, \"rank\": 0.002080445165442114, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The opening ceremony\", \"from\": 3047, \"to\": 3067}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 3119, \"to\": 3135}, {\"ngram\": \"the torch\", \"from\": 3185, \"to\": 3194}, {\"ngram\": \"stars\", \"from\": 3251, \"to\": 3256}, {\"ngram\": \"other countries\", \"from\": 3271, \"to\": 3286}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sometimes the Olympics seem to take place in a city inside a city.\", \"from\": 3325, \"to\": 3391, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3335, \"to\": 3347}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 3361, \"to\": 3366}, {\"ngram\": \"a city\", \"from\": 3370, \"to\": 3376}, {\"ngram\": \"a city\", \"from\": 3384, \"to\": 3390}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only indication that the 2022 Winter Olympics were in China was that the government always seemed to be watching.\", \"from\": 3392, \"to\": 3509, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3450, \"end\": 3455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999839722106374, \"rank\": 1.6003355899087574e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The only indication\", \"from\": 3392, \"to\": 3411}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2022 Winter Olympics\", \"from\": 3417, \"to\": 3441}, {\"ngram\": \"the government\", \"from\": 3465, \"to\": 3479}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Russia built a complex for Sochi that felt like it might all get torn down the day after everybody left.\", \"from\": 3510, \"to\": 3614, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3510, \"end\": 3516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9997900850530527, \"rank\": 0.00020995651624327257, \"text\": \