t just to identify the best.\", \"from\": 3760, \"to\": 3803, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The goal\", \"from\": 3760, \"to\": 3768}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was to experience beauty.\", \"from\": 3804, \"to\": 3832, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"beauty\", \"from\": 3825, \"to\": 3831}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2 Beach volleyball was under the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 3834, \"to\": 3880, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2 Beach volleyball\", \"from\": 3834, \"to\": 3852}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 3863, \"to\": 3879}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Equestrian events often seem out of place at the Olympics and are generally ignored, but at Versailles they seemed like they belonged.\", \"from\": 3881, \"to\": 4015, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Equestrian events\", \"from\": 3881, \"to\": 3898}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 3917, \"to\": 3922}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3926, \"to\": 3938}, {\"ngram\": \"Versailles\", \"from\": 3973, \"to\": 3983}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The various stages added grandeur to events that often seem like afterthoughts.\", \"from\": 4017, \"to\": 4096, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The various stages\", \"from\": 4017, \"to\": 4035}, {\"ngram\": \"grandeur\", \"from\": 4042, \"to\": 4050}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 4054, \"to\": 4060}, {\"ngram\": \"afterthoughts\", \"from\": 4082, \"to\": 4095}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Archery at Invalides, where Napoleon is buried, was breathtaking.\", \"from\": 4097, \"to\": 4162, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4108, \"end\": 4117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Invalides\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.603137138994648e-64, \"text\": \"Invalides\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Invalides\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Invalides\"}, {\"begin\": 4125, \"end\": 4133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.150808872360717e-55, \"text\": \"Napoleon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Archery\", \"from\": 4097, \"to\": 4104}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The purest joy I saw from any athlete during the entire Olympics came from France\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Lisa Barbelin after she won bronze.\", \"from\": 4163, \"to\": 4284, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4249, \"end\": 4262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Barbelin\", \"score\": 0.9999973965511583, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lisa Barbelin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Barbelin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Barbelin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The purest joy\", \"from\": 4163, \"to\": 4177}, {\"ngram\": \"any athlete\", \"from\": 4189, \"to\": 4200}, {\"ngram\": \"the entire Olympics\", \"from\": 4208, \"to\": 4227}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 4277, \"to\": 4283}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The achievement would have been the same anywhere, but it would not have resonated in the same way.\", \"from\": 4285, \"to\": 4384, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The achievement\", \"from\": 4285, \"to\": 4300}, {\"ngram\": \"the same way\", \"from\": 4371, \"to\": 4383}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Food at Olympic venues is generally made of one part old bread and two parts foam packaging.\", \"from\": 4386, \"to\": 4478, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Food\", \"from\": 4386, \"to\": 4390}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic venues\", \"from\": 4394, \"to\": 4408}, {\"ngram\": \"one part old bread\", \"from\": 4430, \"to\": 4448}, {\"ngram\": \"two parts foam packaging\", \"from\": 4453, \"to\": 4477}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In France, it was a proper reflection of the Parisian ethos: Sports should be a lived experience, not just a vehicle for achievement.\", \"from\": 4479, \"to\": 4612, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4482, \"end\": 4488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999998641915319, \"rank\": 1.1547950350792631e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a proper reflection\", \"from\": 4497, \"to\": 4516}, {\"ngram\": \"the Parisian ethos\", \"from\": 4520, \"to\": 4538}, {\"ngram\": \"Sports\", \"from\": 4540, \"to\": 4546}, {\"ngram\": \"a lived experience\", \"from\": 4557, \"to\": 4575}, {\"ngram\": \"not just a vehicle\", \"from\": 4577, \"to\": 4595}, {\"ngram\": \"achievement\", \"from\": 4600, \"to\": 4611}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At times, the Olympics can feel like an act of abuse toward the home country: An expense the people cannot afford, and a party they don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t really want to hold.\", \"from\": 4614, \"to\": 4774, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"times\", \"from\": 4617, \"to\": 4622}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 4624, \"to\": 4636}, {\"ngram\": \"an act\", \"from\": 4651, \"to\": 4657}, {\"ngram\": \"abuse\", \"from\": 4661, \"to\": 4666}, {\"ngram\": \"the home country\", \"from\": 4674, \"to\": 4690}, {\"ngram\": \"An expense\", \"from\": 4692, \"to\": 4702}, {\"ngram\": \"the people\", \"from\": 4703, \"to\": 4713}, {\"ngram\": \"a party\", \"from\": 4733, \"to\": 4740}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At other times, the Olympics can feel like an act of abusefromthe home country: An authoritarian government projecting its preferred image onto athletes who just want to compete.\\u00c2 Whether these Olympics made economic sense for the host country is a fair and worthy question.\", \"from\": 4775, \"to\": 5050, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other times\", \"from\": 4778, \"to\": 4789}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 4791, \"to\": 4803}, {\"ngram\": \"an act\", \"from\": 4818, \"to\": 4824}, {\"ngram\": \"abusefromthe home country\", \"from\": 4828, \"to\": 4853}, {\"ngram\": \"An authoritarian government\", \"from\": 4855, \"to\": 4882}, {\"ngram\": \"its preferred image\", \"from\": 4894, \"to\": 4913}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 4919, \"to\": 4927}, {\"ngram\": \"these Olympics\", \"from\": 4963, \"to\": 4977}, {\"ngram\": \"economic sense\", \"from\": 4983, \"to\": 4997}, {\"ngram\": \"the host country\", \"from\": 5002, \"to\": 5018}, {\"ngram\": \"a fair and worthy question\", \"from\": 5022, \"to\": 5048}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The answer is usually no.\", \"from\": 5051, \"to\": 5076, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The answer\", \"from\": 5051, \"to\": 5061}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Olympics were not just in France; they were of France.\", \"from\": 5077, \"to\": 5139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5111, \"end\": 5117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999998641915319, \"rank\": 1.1547950350792631e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 5132, \"end\": 5138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999998641915319, \"rank\": 1.1547950350792631e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 5081, \"to\": 5093}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The introduction of any athlete from France drew an enormous ovation, but other than boos for American basketball star Joel Embiid, who was repeatedly booed for choosing to represent the U.S. over France, fans seemed to cheer greatness no matter whose flag it honored.\", \"from\": 5140, \"to\": 5408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5177, \"end\": 5183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999998641915319, \"rank\": 1.1547950350792631e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 5234, \"end\": 5242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999994242899, \"rank\": 3.199223926350189e-10, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 5259, \"end\": 5270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joel_Embiid\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Joel Embiid\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joel_Embiid\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joel_Embiid\"}, {\"begin\": 5337, \"end\": 5343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999998641915319, \"rank\": 1.1547950350792631e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The introduction\", \"from\": 5140, \"to\": 5156}, {\"ngram\": \"any athlete\", \"from\": 5160, \"to\": 5171}, {\"ngram\": \"an enormous ovation\", \"from\": 5189, \"to\": 5208}, {\"ngram\": \"boos\", \"from\": 5225, \"to\": 5229}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 5323, \"to\": 5331}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 5345, \"to\": 5349}, {\"ngram\": \"greatness\", \"from\": 5366, \"to\": 5375}, {\"ngram\": \"whose flag\", \"from\": 5386, \"to\": 5396}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Track and field can seem busier than Atlanta\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s airport: A throwing event over here, a leaping event over there, a race snaking in between them.\", \"from\": 5410, \"to\": 5555, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Track\", \"from\": 5410, \"to\": 5415}, {\"ngram\": \"field\", \"from\": 5420, \"to\": 5425}, {\"ngram\": 